&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join Northumbria Healthcare Foundation Trust Safeguarding Team and contribute to the delivery of safeguarding throughout both acute and community services. This post is currently based at North Tyneside General Hospital and is part of a wider safeguarding service which incorporates both safeguarding children and adults safeguarding. The Trust covers a large geographical area, and the successful candidate will need to travel to meet the demands of this post. The team promotes a shared approach to leadership and development; embracing empowerment, motivation, opportunities for learning and creating a positive culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post involves building relationships with teams throughout the Trust, as well as our multi-agency partners, to collaboratively safeguard patients and service users. The successful candidate will have a key role in providing training for practitioners such as Midwives, nurses, talking therapies . Additionally, there will be some opportunity to contribute to the delivery of group supervisions to a variety of teams across the Trust, and also to design and deliver aspects of both multi-agency and single agency safeguarding training alongside individual / team packages of support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: jill wood&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: named midwife safeguarding children&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address jill.wood6@northumbria-healkthcare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 07747764728&lt;/p&gt;
